                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14480042" author="paulk" created="Wed, 14 Nov 2012 05:37:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are correct that the code should be checking &lt;tt&gt;isAttributeValue&lt;/tt&gt; but since quotes don&apos;t need to escaped would you regard it is a weird but benign quirk of the created content? I am not saying we won&apos;t fix it but just saying that the fix might be to not quote at all for element text?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14473452" author="quidryan" created="Wed, 14 Nov 2012 12:44:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Excellent point, I got caught up with the output not matching what I thought, but you&apos;re right that it&apos;s reasonable to not escape a quote in the body.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14480043" author="paulk" created="Fri, 16 Nov 2012 23:51:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed by skipping escaping for apostrophes and quotes in element text. Thanks for spotting the anomaly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
